That's not true.  I wear the eyepatch of a friend who won it a long time ago.  It was never sold.  It never will be.  In the least it will be passed on to a friend or a twink, but such an old item and a gift means a lot to me, and even if I got better like NToV loot, I would not sell it.  <br>
<br>
Lachdenen grew out of his RBB replacing a 31% haste item with a 40% epic haste item.  It didnt take long, but its a situation that in context is repeated.  A warrior that comes to a raid as a gimpy level 43 with crustacean armor and wins an RBB might some day be equipped with full HoT armor and get a Cloak of Flames to replace his RBB.  In this situation its the same thing, it just took longer.  <br>
<br>
But not all items are like that.  You know many monks that can top a 10-slot 100% redux pack that weighs .4?  Most monks I know that come would TREASURE that bag for their life.  Not everyone is going to join IvM or EW.  Odds are likely that a melee that wins an RBB and doesnt upgrade to epic haste will be wearing that a LONG time before they can upgrade 4% of that haste with a CoF.<br>
<br>
Times change, people grow, and I can accept that.  But all of these items will NOT be sold.  Some will be kept forever and some will be discarded once useless (Rez staff with no charges) or passed on to twinks (my patch).  Some are sought by high level players.. I know several wizzies interested in the Cloak now, and I doubt anyone with decent nuking power will EVER ditch a cloak with Improved Damage not true and even I can be a testament to that.III on it.<br>
<br>
Believing that all items are sold is skewing the facts, its simply <br>
<br>
